<item>
 <title>A.5.b. Course Syllabus</title>
 <link>https://www.middlebury.edu/old-about/old-handbook/iv.-policies-for-the-institute/a.-academic-policies/a.5.-instruction/a.5.b.-course-syllabus/node/590409</link>
 <description>&lt;div class=&quot;field field-name-body field-type-text-with-summary field-label-hidden&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;field-items&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;field-item even&quot;&gt;&lt;p&gt;The course syllabus communicates the overall expectations that the faculty has for student work. It is issued by the instructor at the beginning of every course taught at the Middlebury Institute and is subject to change as determined by the instructor with advance notice and due respect to fairness to the students as a whole. Â &lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;The course syllabus shall include: general course information, instructor information (contact information, office hours), a course description, course objective(s), instructional methodology, assessment of students, grading methodologies and criteria, a course reading list, a course outline, and a calendar.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;</description>
